Entries.default: "Hey there, aimico. Welcome to the land of giants, right? I've never felt quite so small."
Entries.female: "Hey there, aimica. Welcome to the land of giants, right? I've never felt quite so small."

Entries.default: "Fancy a look at the wares, my friend?"
"You're a bit out of the way, aren't you?"
"Let me see what you have."
"Best goods on the island."
"Did you see the fight between Rinco and Mokeha?"

"Did I see it? Best night of my life. She just-" 

She jabs vaguely at the air, pretending to throw punches.

"...and he was out like a snuffed candle, poor bastard. I assumed he was being his usual charming self. How he and the wife get on so well, I have no idea." 

"Why do you ask?"
"Do you know how it started?"
"Not really. I saw the Huana woman bearing down on him, looking like trouble. They argued for a bit. His buddies were dragging him down the road not long after that."
"Never mind."
She nods, watching you expectantly.
"Cozy spot, right? Not much competition, apart from the basket lady. And the Huana have coin to spend and goods to trade, same as the rest."
[Leave] "Farewell."
"Any chance you have something Mokeha might like?"
"You mean she likes things?" "I joke, I joke. She is so serious. Like the guards back in Port Maje."

"So, I have this carving? All the way from Neketaka. They churn them out, easy.

"She won't know that."
"How much?"
"Ah, just take it. I have a hundred. Tell Mokeha she is getting better at cards."
"Maybe not."
"Well, something for you, then? Anything you like."
"Please! Don't hurt me! I don't have anything to do with it!"
